abstract: It's Love, Angel, Music, and Baby No.2 for Gwen Stefani , who gave birth to Zuma Nesta Rock this week. The boy weighed 8 pounds 5 ounces (about 3.9 kilograms), and "mother, baby and family are all happy and healthy," a publicist said in a statement. The pop singer and her husband, the rocker Gavin Rossdale , were married in 2002 and have a son, Kingston , born in May 2006. Rossdale also has an 18-year-old daughter with Pearl Lowe , the former frontwoman of 1990s band Powder. Stefani's last album, "The Sweet Escape," was released in 2006, a follow-up to the multiplatinum 2004 album "Love. Angel. Music. Baby."

abstract: Christian Bale, Batman in "The Dark Knight," won't be charged in an alleged assault on his mother and sister, in part because they didn't want to press the matter but also for lack of sufficient evidence, prosecutors have said. The Crown Prosecution Service in London ordered the police not to take any further action, saying there was insufficient evidence to make a conviction realistic. The service said in a statement that it treats domestic incidents seriously, but feels it's important "that the views of complainants are also taken into account when making decisions in such cases." Bale, who denies the allegation, said through his spokeswoman he was relieved the issue had been settled. (AP)

abstract: An Anglican civil war over a gay American bishop is averted. For now. Barely.
snippet: An Anglican civil war over a gay American bishop is averted. For now. Barely.
lead_paragraph: CANTERBURY, England â€” For a man at the heart of a bitter dispute that threatens to sunder the Anglican communion, Bishop Gene Robinson seems more relaxed than almost any of the 650 bishops and archbishops gathered for the Lambeth Conference, the once-a-decade assembly that brings together the leaders of an estimated 80 million Anglicans worldwide.
